es sitting on a chair without a chair of course and hence popularly called the Chair Pose.";i:10;s:66:"Utkatasana is relatively simple to perform at the same time needs.";i:11;s:110:"This is an important pose in yoga for energizing the entire body and promoting creativity and mental strength.";i:12;s:85:"Chair pose is also known as fierce pose powerful pose or in Bikram yoga awkward pose.";i:13;s:32:"The Sanskrit name is utkatasana.";i:14;s:135:"Utkatasana is also called chair pose because the posture of the person performing this asana is similar to a person sitting in a chair.";i:15;s:176:"Utkatasana is a Sanskrit language word that is made up of two words in which the first word is Utkat which means wild or fierce the second word meaning Asana which means Mudra.";i:16;s:71:"In this same way we go down in chair pose to sit on an invisible chair.";i:17;s:116:"English translation of this pose is simple but the Sanskrit one has many meanings and interpretations to understand.";i:18;s:34:"Chair symbolizes a seat or throne.";i:19;s:55:"Chair Yoga pose is also known as Utkatasna in Sanskrit.";i:20;s:93:"The word Utkatasana comprises of two words Utkata means intense and Asana means Yoga posture.";i:21;s:51:"Utkatasana is also pronounced as OOT-kah-TAHS-anna.";i:22;s:53:"Yoga chair pose is just like an imaginary chair pose.";i:23;s:54:"Inhale and raise your arms perpendicular to the floor.";i:24;s:68:"Either keep the arms parallel palms facing inward or join the palms.";i:25;s:97:"Exhale and bend your knees trying to take the thighs as nearly parallel to the floor as possible.";i:26;s:45:"The knees will project out over the feet and.";i:27;s:50:"Yoga Poses Meditations Sequences and Free Classes.";i:28;s:72:"Utkaṭāsana Chair Pose is a standing asana in modern yoga as exercise.";i:29;s:52:"It was a low squatting asana in medieval hatha yoga.";i:30;s:22:"Chair pose Utkatasana.";i:31;s:23:"Mountain pose Tadasana.";i:32;s:28:"Crescent lunge Anjenayasana.";i:33;s:75:"One-Foote